        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A mother from a rural community in Maharashtra brings her 8-year-old child to the regional hospital. The child has been suffering from severe bone pain, fever, and noticeable yellowing of the skin. On examination the child had the following clinical findings. Laboratory analysis, including a peripheral blood smear, indicates microcytic anemia, with red blood cells demonstrating a distinctive crescent shape and the presence of target cells. With regard to the child&#39;s condition, which of the following statements is incorrect?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/03/29/picture21_OAjvxMa.jpg\" style=\"height:202px; width:300px\" /></span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q5513865",
      "question_audio": null,
